<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-07T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-07T22:00:00-05:00" n="687" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/572</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-07T22:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1918, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.42 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The contract between the Shipping Board and the Peruvian Government
                                concerning interned German ships was approved by Peruvian Congress
                                September 5, signed the 6th, and on same night
                                    <persName>Gardner</persName> departed with two of them.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MB1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>